  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The goal of this study is to use the tissues from the explanted lungs in order to better
      study the cause of pulmonary fibrosis at a cellular level.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Pulmonary Fibrosis involves scarring of the lung. Gradually, the air sacs of the lungs
      become replaced by fibrotic tissue. The most current thinking is that the fibrotic process
      is a reaction to tiny injury to the lung. When the scar forms, the tissue becomes thicker
      causing a permanent loss of the tissue's ability to carry oxygen into the bloodstream.

      We need to obtain lung tissue from patients without pulmonary fibrosis and compare it to
      lung tissue from patients with pulmonary fibrosis.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
